Video | Morgan Stanley Small Cap TV: Asia Pacific Results takeaways, HUB, NWL
In this video, we discuss our latest thoughts on AD8, HUB and NWL.
MORGAN STANLEY AUSTRALIA LIMITED+
AUSTRALIA EMERGING COMPANIES

Audinate Group Ltd: Improving into FY26 and FY27 (18 August 2025)  Hub24 Ltd: FY25 in- line, strong start to FY26 (18 August 2025)  Netwealth Group Ltd: Reinvesting in the long term (21 August 2025)
Animate Group Ltd (AD8.AX) Base case - average of SOTP and DCF: A \(\) 11\$
Audio (core business) - 10x FY26e: Structural penetration story with growth durability.
Video - 10x FY26e: nascent large opportunity with long runway. Recent adoption data points also look strong.
Software - 10x FY26e: early- stage penetration and synergies with Audio and Video support multiple above Software peer average but below group.
DCF: WACC 10.8%, terminal growth rate 4%.
- Meaningful acceleration in Audio- Video sales acceleration- Expansion of Software opportunity- Adjacencies that further expand TAM- Shift to FCF generation
- Macro weakness causes quicker deceleration in growth and cash losses- Execution missteps in Video mean slow ramp-up- Potential increase in competition- Key management churn

Approximate midpoint of our fundamental value range, derived from two methodologies - DCF and P/E. We use DCF to capture the long- term cash flow generation of the business. We use P/E to measure the relative attractiveness versus HUB's long- term history and comparable companies.
i) DCF: WACC 8.1%, terminal growth rate 3.0%
ii) P/E: 70x FY26E (~4-0% premium to HUB's 5- year average c.50x)
- Faster industry growth- Market share gains
Revenue margin increase  - EBITDA margin expansion  - Balance sheet used for organic, M&A or returned to shareholders  - Monetisation of Adjacencies e.g. MyProsperity, Class, HUBconnect
Slower industry growth  - Market share gains moderate  - Ongoing revenue margin compression  - Higher reinvestment  - P/E multiple compression

Approximate midpoint (rounded to the nearest 25c) of our fundamental value range, derived from two methodologies – DCF and P/E. We use DCF to capture the long- term cash flow generation of the business. We use P/E to measure the relative attractiveness versus NWL's long- term history and comparable companies.
i) DCF: WACC 8.0%, terminal growth rate 3.0%
ii) P/E: 70x FY27E (~25% premium to five- year average 55x)
Faster industry growth  - Market share gains  - Revenue margin increase  - EBITDA margin expansion  - Balance sheet used for organic M&A or returned to shareholders
Negative market movements  - Market share gains moderate  - Ongoing revenue margin compression  - Higher reinvestment  - P/E multiple compression

Overweight (O). The stock's total return is expected to exceed the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.

Equal-weight (E). The stock's total return is expected to be in line with the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.

Not-Rated (NR). Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.

Underweight (U). The stock's total return is expected to be below the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.
Unless otherwise specified, the time frame for price targets included in Morgan Stanley Research is 12 to 18 months.
Attractive (A): The analyst expects the performance of his or her industry coverage universe over the next 12- 18 months to be attractive vs. the relevant broad market benchmark, as indicated below.

In-Line (I): The analyst expects the performance of his or her industry coverage universe over the next 12- 18 months to be in line with the relevant broad market benchmark, as indicated below. Cautious (C): The analyst views the performance of his or her industry coverage universe over the next 12- 18 months with caution vs. the relevant broad market benchmark, as indicated below. Benchmarks for each region are as follows: North America - S&P 500; Latin America - relevant MSCI country index or MSCI Latin America Index; Europe - MSCI Europe; Japan - TOPIX; Asia - relevant MSCI country index or MSCI sub-regional index or MSCI AC Asia Pacific ex Japan Index.
